Harry N. Pefanis 

		
		President and COO, 

	
		 Plains All American Pipeline, L.P. 	

 
Last Updated: 01/31/2017 



Executive Summary
Pefanis is a 30-year veteran of the energy industry. He has worked at various PAA subsidiaries since 1983 and has been President and COO since 1998. He is responsible for executing the Company's strategy, overseeing its day-to-day operations and identifying areas for future expansion. 
Current Focus

Strategic acquisition: In January 2017, Plains All American Pipeline agreed to acquire 100% of the equity interests of Alpha Holding Company, which indirectly owns the Alpha Crude Connector (ACC) gathering system locate 
Biographical Highlights

Born c. 1958 in Buffalo, New York
Pefanis earned a BBA degree in accounting from the University of Oklahoma in 1979. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, Crude Oil Advisory Committee, New York Mercantile Exchange (1996-2003)
Member, Board of Directors, Settoon Towing 
 





